        %p
          Definitions:
        %ul.info
          %li “First Party” Cookie – A cookie placed by this Site
          %li “Third Party” Cookie – A cookie placed by another domain (e.g. not this Site)
          %li “Permanent” Cookie – The cookie information is permanently stored on your device
          %li “Temporary” Cookie – The cookie information is stored for a defined period on your device (e.g. six months)
          %li “Session” Cookie – The cookie information is temporarily stored in your web browser’s memory
          %li Implied Consent – You are deemed to have given your consent by continuing to use this Site or McKinsey Academy after having had this Privacy Policy made available to you
          %li Explicit Consent – You specifically agree to the use of cookies after having had this Privacy Policy made available to you
          %li “Strictly Necessary” Cookies – These cookies are required so the Site can function. No consent is required

        %p.style-2 Is personally-identifiable information disclosed to third parties?
        %p We shall not intentionally disclose or transfer (and shall take reasonable steps to prevent the unauthorized or accidental disclosure of) your personally-identifiable information to third parties (i.e., persons that are not employees or contractors of McKinsey & Company, Inc. or its affiliates) without your consent, whether for such third parties’ marketing purposes or otherwise, except as follows:
        %p
          %ul.info
            %li
              We may provide access to your personally-identifiable information to third party vendors or service providers engaged by McKinsey to provide services related to McKinsey Academy or the Site (including edX, as more particularly described in Section 8 of the Terms); provided that each such third party agree to maintain the confidentiality of such information in a manner consistent with this Privacy Policy. Each such third party is an “authorized third party service provider.”
            %li
              We may provide access to certain of your personally-identifiable information to your Sponsoring Organization as described elsewhere in this Privacy Policy.
            %li
              We may also be compelled to surrender personal user or customer information, including personally-identifiable information, to legal authorities (including to law enforcement and/or national security authorities) without express user consent if presented with a court subpoena or similar legal order, or as required or permitted by the laws, rules, and regulations of any applicable jurisdiction. 
            %li
              Also, in the event of a violation of the Terms or any other terms on this Site or to which you agree in connection with your use of McKinsey Academy, including but not limited to a violation of any restrictions on use of McKinsey Academy Content or your provision of User Content, McKinsey may disclose personal user or customer information, including personally-identifiable information, to affected parties and legal authorities in furtherance of potential or on-going legal proceedings.

        %p.style-2 Surveys
        %p
          If you participate in a survey, all of our research results are publically reported as totals or in other aggregated form and no information about you as an individual respondent is made public. However, we will be able to identify individual respondents by their email address, and may follow-up with individuals for additional information to improve the overall McKinsey Academy experience. If you prefer that we not follow up with you on your survey responses please contact us at the address listed below in the Contact Us section of this Privacy Policy.
        %p.style-2 User disclosure
        %p
          You should be aware that whenever you publicly disclose information online, even to a limited group of recipients (for example, other users who are enrolled in the same McKinsey Academy course as you) that information could be collected and used by others. McKinsey is not responsible for any action or policies of any third parties, including other McKinsey Academy users, who collect information that users disclose to such third parties in connection with their use of McKinsey Academy or the Site.
        %p.style-2 Link to third-party sites
        %p
          McKinsey may provide links to third-party Web sites or information as a service to our users. If you use these links, you will leave this Site. Such links do not constitute or imply an endorsement, sponsorship, or recommendation by McKinsey of the third party, the third party web site, or the information contained therein, and McKinsey shall not be responsible or liable for your use thereof. Such use shall be subject to the terms of use and privacy policies applicable to those sites. 
        %p.style-2 Security
        %p
          McKinsey has implemented generally accepted standards of technology and operational security in order to protect your personally-identifiable information from loss, misuse, alteration, or destruction. Only authorized McKinsey personnel and contractors and authorized third party service providers are provided access to personally-identifiable information, and these employees, contractors and service providers are required to treat this information as confidential. Despite these precautions, McKinsey, however, cannot guarantee that unauthorized persons will not obtain access to your personally-identifiable information. If you become aware that any of your personally-identifiable information provided in connection with McKinsey Academy or this Site may have been compromised, please contact us immediately at the address listed below in the Contact Us section of this Privacy Policy.
        %p.style-2 Transborder hosting and transfer of information
        %p
          Personally-identifiable information collected on the Site or otherwise through McKinsey Academy may be transferred to and processed by from time to time to McKinsey offices or personnel, or to third parties including authorized third party service providers, located throughout the world, and the Site may be viewed and hosted by McKinsey or its service providers anywhere in the world, including countries that may not have the same data protection laws as are found in your country of residence. By using McKinsey Academy or the Site and providing us with your information, you voluntarily consent to such transborder transfer, processing and hosting of such information.
        %p.style-2 Data Retention Policy
        %p
          McKinsey stores personally-identifiable information for various purposes as notified to you in this Privacy Policy and in the Terms. For each of these different purposes, McKinsey only retains the personally-identifiable information for so long as it is serving its notified purpose.
        %p
          More specifically, McKinsey retains personally-identifiable information for:

        %table
          %thead
            %tr
              %th System
              %th Data Retention Purpose
              %th Retention Period
          %tbody
            %tr
              %td McKinseyAcademy.com
              %td Your contact details and other User Account Information (as such term is defined in the Terms) will be collected for the purpose of registering and accessing the course.
              %td Indefinitely – Your contact details will be retained indefinitely.

            %tr
              %td McKinseyAcademy.com
              %td User forums and boards – To provide an environment for the open exchange of ideas.
              %td Indefinitely - Any personally-identifiable information made publicly available on user forums or boards will remain available indefinitely.

            %tr
