              %td Retain User Content (as such term is defined in the Terms)
              %td Indefinitely – for research, analysis and to develop or enhance Aggregate Site Information

        %p.style-2 Access and Opt-Out
        %p
          If you consent to our collection, use, and disclosure of your personally-identifiable information, including User Account Information and Participation Data, you may request that we provide you with the personally-identifiable information that McKinsey has about you to ensure that it is accurate or for other reasons allowed under applicable law.  McKinsey will provide you with access to your personally-identifiable information in our possession to the extent required by applicable law. Please note there may be times when we might be unable to do so, such as when (a) disclosing your information may reveal confidential information or personally-identifiable information about someone else, if we are unable to separate it; (b) your personally-identifiable information has been de-identified, anonymized and/or aggregated in such a way that we are unable to identify it as yours without undue burden or expense; or (c) providing access is prohibitively costly.
        %p
          You may revoke your consent to the collection, use and/or disclosure of your personally-identifiable information at any time by contacting McKinsey at the address listed below. Please note that if you revoke your consent certain features of McKinsey Academy and/or the Site, including courses in which you are currently enrolled, may no longer be able to be made available to you as they rely on the collection, use and/or disclosure of your personally-identifiable information. You may also ask us to remove or delete your personally-identifiable information in our possession, and where required by applicable law we will do so promptly and to the extent we are technically able. Please note there may be times when we might be unable to do so, such as when your personally-identifiable information has been de-identified, anonymized and/or aggregated in such a way that we are unable to identify it as yours without undue burden or expense (including, by way of example, where your personally-identifiable information has been incorporated into or used to help create Aggregate Site Information) or where we are required by applicable law to retain your personal-identifiable information.
        %p.style-2 Children
        %p
          We understand the importance of protecting children's privacy, especially in an on-line environment. Neither McKinsey Academy nor the Site is designed for or directed at children 13 years of age or younger, and we will not intentionally collect or maintain information about anyone under this age.
        %p.style-2 Consent; changes to privacy policy
        %p
          By using McKinsey Academy or this Site, you consent to the collection, use, and storage of your information, including your personally-identifiable information and personal data, by us in the manner described in this Privacy Policy, the Terms and elsewhere on the Site. We reserve the right to make changes to this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will alert you to any such changes by updating this Privacy Policy as made available on the Site. This Privacy Policy was last updated on December 1, 2016.
